Package: blusteR
Type: Package
Title: B-Cell Lymphocyte Interaction by Paratope Hotspots
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: person("blusteR", "Developer", email = "bluster@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Clusters B-cell receptor (BCR) sequences by shared antigen-binding
    specificity, adapting the GLIPH2 paradigm (Huang et al., 2020) to the unique
    biology of antibodies.
    blusteR discovers convergent CDR3 motifs in heavy- and light-chain sequences,
    scores global CDR3 similarity with somatic-hypermutation-aware metrics, tests
    enrichment against the Observed Antibody Space (OAS) reference, and annotates
    clusters with known B-cell epitopes from IEDB and structural data from SAbDab.
    Accepts 10X Genomics VDJ output and scRepertoire combined-contigs objects
    natively.
